## The Change

Replace the current 3-line `GET /users` handler:
```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json(users);
});
```

With this paginated version:
```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit);

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

**Key design points:**
- `parseInt(...) || default` handles missing/non-numeric params gracefully
- `Math.max(1, ...)` clamps negative/zero values to 1
- `users.slice(start, start + limit)` returns `[]` automatically when `start >= 15` (out-of-range page) — no extra branch needed
- `GET /users/:id` is completely untouched

